body:
`Verilator 4.225 devel rev v4.224-49-ge0b61cea`

  ```verilog
module tjo();                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   
initial begin                                                                                                                                                                                                                           
    string fail_str = "foo";                                                                                                                                                                                                              
    $sformat(fail_str, "%s", fail_str);                                                                                                                                                                                                   
    $sformat(fail_str, "%s", fail_str);                                                                                                                                                                                                        
    $display(fail_str);                                                                                                                                                                                                                   
end                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                
endmodule
```

I expect the the string "foo" to be printed out, but instead the empty string is printed.

I found that the overwriting of the string is done here, the `output` string is cleared before it is read by `vl_vsformat`:

https://github.com/verilator/verilator/blob/e0b61ceabd76d2fd3aae0a1ff1bd522e307de409/include/verilated.cpp#L1460-L1467

A possible solution would be to not clear the output string, and instead use a new string that is then copied to the output string:

```cpp
void VL_SFORMAT_X(int obits_ignored, std::string& output, const char* formatp, ...) VL_MT_SAFE {
    if (obits_ignored) {}
    static VL_THREAD_LOCAL std::string t_output;  // static only for speed
    t_output = "";
    va_list ap;
    va_start(ap, formatp);
    _vl_vsformat(t_output, formatp, ap);
    va_end(ap);

    output = t_output;
}
```
I tried this and it seems to work for this simple case.

Do you want me to create a merge request with this change?
